{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"1-Add-the-SDK","text":"1. Add the SDK","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"YEOFR"}]},{"text":" Swift package","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"https:\/\/github.com\/YEOMessaging\/YEOFR-SPM","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") to your project, pinned to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"exact version ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.5.8"}]},{"text":", then ","type":"text"},{"code":"import YEOFR","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The binary is ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"arm64","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"device-only","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — it does not run on the simulator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"2-Pilot-unlock-for-non-YEO-bundle-IDs","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"2. Pilot unlock for non-YEO bundle IDs"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"YEOFR is gated to YEO-owned apps by default; a non-YEO bundle id aborts on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"construction. Evaluation customers get a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"temporary unlock code","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bypasses the gate during a fixed pilot window — email"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"christo@yeomessaging.com"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to request one. Pass it to the initializer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(step 3). YEO-owned apps pass the gate natively and do not need a code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"3. Drive everything with `FaceTrustService`","type":"heading","anchor":"3-Drive-everything-with-FaceTrustService","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is the turnkey entry point. It owns the engine, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"camera, the fused-trust pipeline (face recognition + liveness CNN +"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TrueDepth), the identity gate, and tracker persistence, and exposes two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"streams: one for live trust verdicts and one for guided enrolment."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import YEOFR","","let service = FaceTrustService(pilotUnlockCode: \"YOUR-PILOT-CODE\")","","\/\/ Attach the preview to an AVCaptureVideoPreviewLayer:","\/\/   previewLayer.session = service.previewSession","","try await service.start()    \/\/ warm-up, restore enrolment, arm gate, start camera"]},{"text":"4. Enrol a face","level":2,"anchor":"4-Enrol-a-face","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"enroll(name:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" runs a short guided capture, persists the gallery, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"re-arms the identity gate. Iterate the returned stream to coach the user:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["for await step in service.enroll(name: \"Alice\") {","    switch step.phase {","    case .capturing: show(step.prompt, progress: step.poseProgress)","    case .completed: dismiss()","    case .failed:    show(step.prompt)","    @unknown default: break","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A single front pose is enough to separate the enrolled user from other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"people. Pass ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poses: PoseTarget.lightingAwareGallerySequence"},{"type":"text","text":" to also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capture off-axis poses + a lighting pass, which improves recall as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user turns their head."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"5-Run-live-recognition","type":"heading","text":"5. Run live recognition"},{"code":["for await update in service.updates() {","    switch update.status {","    case .trusted:    badge(\"TRUSTED — \\(update.matchedName ?? \"\")\", .green)","    case .notTrusted: badge(\"NOT TRUSTED\", .red)","    case .badFraming: badge(\"ADJUST FRAMING\", .orange)","    case .noFace:     badge(\"NO FACE\", .gray)","    @unknown default: break","    }","    \/\/ update.livenessGenuine \/ update.depthIsThreeD are the contributing signals.","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update.status == .trusted"},{"text":" already fuses face recognition, liveness, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TrueDepth, with framing applied — you never pick a similarity threshold,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and you never touch the identity gate (forgetting it would collapse trust","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to liveness + depth, so any live face would pass). The enrolled gallery is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"saved across launches automatically; ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"service.enrolledName"},{"text":" reflects who is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"enrolled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"See also","type":"heading","anchor":"See-also"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A complete, runnable SwiftUI app lives in the package’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"Examples\/FRPilot","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService","type":"reference"},{"text":" — full API.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustUpdate","isActive":true},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/EnrollmentProgress","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" — the stream payloads.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/quickstart"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/quickstart"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/QuickStart"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Getting-started","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService"],"title":"Getting started"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"YEOFR"}],"role":"article","title":"QuickStart"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Recognise the enrolled user and reject everyone else, in a few lines."}],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustService/updates()":{"url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustservice\/updates()","type":"topic","title":"updates()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"updates"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"AsyncStream"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:5YEOFR15FaceTrustUpdateV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"FaceTrustUpdate"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Per-frame trust verdicts for the recognition UI. Call once and iterate;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the stream finishes on ","type":"text"},{"code":"stop()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Newest-wins (the underlying camera","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stream drops stale frames), so a slow consumer can’t back up memory.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/updates()","role":"symbol"},"doc://com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"On-device face recognition with fused liveness and TrueDepth anti-spoofing."}],"title":"YEOFR","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR","kind":"symbol"},"doc://com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR/documentation/YEOFR/FaceTrustService/enroll(name:poses:)":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Enrol "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"type":"text","text":" from the live camera and return a stream of capture"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. The existing frame loop drives the gallery walk; on completion"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the service persists the gallery, refreshes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enrolledName"},{"type":"text","text":", resets the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trust pipeline against the fresh gallery, and re-arms the identity gate —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the consumer does none of that."}],"title":"enroll(name:poses:)","url":"\/documentation\/yeofr\/facetrustservice\/enroll(name:poses:)","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.youreyeonly.yeofr.YEOFR\/documentation\/YEOFR\/FaceTrustService\/enroll(name:poses:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"enroll","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"name","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIden